{
  "name": "Alien Mind — Callback Telegram",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 📨 Alien Mind — Callback Telegram\n\nGestisce le 4 azioni inline button del messaggio di review:\n\n- **✅ Approva** → sposta file in cartella `approved` su Drive, UPDATE `posts.status='approved'`, conferma\n- **🔄 Rigenera img** → riusa la stessa frase, lancia il workflow principale via Execute Workflow (regenera solo l'immagine)\n- **🔁 Cambia frase** → lancia il workflow principale fresh (nuova frase + nuova immagine)\n- **❌ Scarta** → cancella file da Drive, UPDATE `posts.status='rejected'`, conferma\n\n**Webhook**: POST /webhook/alien-mind-callback\n\nDopo l'import, **registra il webhook su Telegram**:\n```\ncurl 'https://api.telegram.org/bot<TOKEN>/setWebhook?url=<WEBHOOK_URL>/webhook/alien-mind-callback'\n```\n\n**Caveat**: il nodo \"Execute alien-mind-pipeline\" referenzia il workflow per ID. Dopo aver importato il workflow principale, aggiorna l'ID nel nodo (n8n te lo chiede al primo run).",
        "height": 460,
        "width": 540
      },
      "id": "stickyHeader",
      "name": "📋 Header",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-200, -200]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "httpMethod": "POST",
        "path": "alien-mind-callback",
        "responseMode": "onReceived",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "webhook",
      "name": "Webhook Telegram",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.webhook",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [400, 380],
      "webhookId": "alien-mind-callback"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "language": "javaScript",
        "jsCode": "// Parsa il callback_query Telegram. Estrai action, post_id, e i metadati per editare il messaggio dopo.\nconst body = $input.first().json.body || $input.first().json;\nconst cq = body.callback_query;\n\nif (!cq || !cq.data) {\n  // Update non-callback (es. messaggio ordinario): non gestito.\n  throw new Error('Update Telegram senza callback_query.data — payload: ' + JSON.stringify(body).slice(0, 300));\n}\n\nconst [action, postIdStr] = String(cq.data).split(':');\nconst post_id = parseInt(postIdStr, 10);\n\nif (!Number.isFinite(post_id) || !['approve','regen','change','discard'].includes(action)) {\n  throw new Error('callback_data non riconosciuto: ' + cq.data);\n}\n\n// Carica i dettagli del post + quote dal DB.\nconst Database = require('better-sqlite3');\nconst DB_PATH = process.env.QUOTES_DB_PATH || '/data/database/quotes.db';\nconst db = new Database(DB_PATH, { readonly: true });\nlet post, quote;\ntry {\n  post = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM posts WHERE id = ?').get(post_id);\n  if (!post) throw new Error('Post non trovato: id=' + post_id);\n\n  const table = post.quote_source === 'curated' ? 'quotes' : 'generated_quotes';\n  quote = db.prepare(`SELECT * FROM ${table} WHERE id = ?`).get(post.quote_id);\n} finally {\n  db.close();\n}\n\n// Estrai il drive file_id dall'URL (formato webViewLink: https://drive.google.com/file/d/<ID>/view)\nlet drive_file_id = null;\nif (post.image_url_drive) {\n  const m1 = post.image_url_drive.match(/\\/d\\/([^\\/?]+)/);\n  const m2 = post.image_url_drive.match(/[?&]id=([^&]+)/);\n  drive_file_id = (m1 && m1[1]) || (m2 && m2[1]) || null;\n}\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    action,\n    post_id,\n    post_status: post.status,\n    quote_source: post.quote_source,\n    drive_file_id,\n    drive_url: post.image_url_drive,\n    // Quote details (utili per regen)\n    quote_id:   quote ? quote.id : null,\n    quote_text: quote ? quote.text : null,\n    author:     quote ? quote.author : null,\n    source:     quote ? quote.source : null,\n    theme:      quote ? quote.theme : null,\n    mood:       quote ? quote.mood : null,\n    // Meta Telegram per answerCallbackQuery + editMessage\n    callback_query_id: cq.id,\n    chat_id:    cq.message && cq.message.chat ? cq.message.chat.id : null,\n    message_id: cq.message ? cq.message.message_id : null\n  }\n}];\n"
      },
      "id": "codeParse",
      "name": "Parse callback + load post",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [620, 380]
